Business Brief -- Boeing Co.:
   Firm Notifies 2,438 Workers
   Of the Possibility of Layoffs
Boeing, which employs 104,000 in its home state and
156,000 companywide, has said it expects this year to cut its
employment rolls in Washington state by about 6,500 and by
another 1,500 at its Wichita, Kan., plant. The company has
already issued a total of about 4,200 notices, and has laid
off 323 workers, the spokesman said.